Looking for commanders to brew by CMC, and I just noticed that MonoBlack and MonoBlue are the only colors without a commander at CMC=1

Every two-color combination has a Commander CMC=2.
And for the tri-colors, all of them have one at CMC=3. 
If you get particular:
For the wedges, Jeskai doesn’t have a URW costed General
For the shards, Grixis and Jund don’t have one that’s not from Legends (arbitrary I know.)
so you wanna build commanders with no generic mana in their mana cost essentially?
require one of each of their colors?
or were just browsing with that filter
Just browsing, really.
It started as noticing the lack of MonoU and MonoB and then it was just curiosity.
I really like low CMC commanders though, and I think there is something elegant about legends that cost only their colors
I’d really love to see what a monoBlack one drop legend would look like though.
